\subsection{Subclassing}{

Subclasses should call \code{super$initialize(name, description, set_only)}
and then register their own arguments with \verb{$new_argument()}. The parent
constructor sets \verb{$provides} to \code{"tree search"} and initialises
\verb{$set_only}.
}

\subsection{Set-only mode}{

When \verb{$set_only} is \code{TRUE}, \verb{$render()} appends a colon to the command
name (e.g., \verb{mult:}) instead of an equals sign (\verb{mult=}). This
configures parameters in TNT without triggering execution. Set-only mode
is applied automatically by \link{ExtraSearchMethodsCommand} when
orchestrating sub-strategies.
}

\subsection{Default values}{\tabular{ll}{
   Parameter \tab Default \cr
   \code{set_only} \tab \code{FALSE} \cr
}

}

\subsection{Queue integration}{

Calling \verb{$enqueue()} adds this command to a \link{CommandQueue} at priority
\code{501}. When \verb{$set_only} is \code{FALSE}, it also enqueues:
\itemize{
\item A \link{CollapseTreesCommand} at priority \code{600}.
\item A \link{TreePlottingCommand} at priority \code{601}.
}
}
